VThe programme began with a brief but impressive vocal concert by Manda Krishna Mohan, an able singer and staffer of the music college. He has a tuneful voice and fine manodharmam. Krishna Mohan renderedSogasu Jooda TaramainKannadagowla, Devadi Devaof Mysore Vasudevachar inSunada Vinodini,Narayanate Namo Namoof Annamayya inBehagand anAshtapadi(Radhika Krishna) inChakravakam.The last item of the evening was a melodious instrumental ensemble with the participation of K.S. Govindarajan, principal of the music college on the veena, lecturer V. Krishnaveni on the violin, Indrakeeladri Sarma on flute, M. Vijayakumar on mridangam and V. Amritkumar on tabla.The group playedNatakuranji varnam,Vatapi(Hamsadhvani), thepancharatna keertanaEndaro(Sriragam), Patnam&#8217;sRaghuvamsa Sudhambudhi(Kadana Kutuhalam) and Annamayya&#8217;sAdigo AlladigoinMadhyamavathiwith admirable co-ordination.
